	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>New Orleans</placeName> <date>May 19&#44; 1854</date></p>
				<p><addressee>Revd Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Phi<hi rend="sup">la</hi></placeName> Dear Sir</p>
				
				<p>Not aware of the Value of your last<lb/> shipment &#38; with out this knowledge of<lb/> the actual Contents I have not insured<lb/> In <sic>refering</sic> to your advice of the <date>10th</date> I <sic>omited</sic><lb/> to say I beg to decline sending any Bibles<lb/> to <placeName>Texas</placeName> as the chances are you would never<lb/> hear from them again&#44; If I could pack them<lb/> with <persName>Harmans</persName> goods at any time I should<lb/> feel sure of then safely but not otherwise.  I<lb/> wait <persName>Mr Osterman&#39;s</persName> <sic>adviseing</sic> me He will<lb/> receive the 2 Bibles are I send them &#38; hope<lb/> you have written to Him&#44; If opportunity<lb/> offers will send <persName>Dr Mayer</persName> Book to <placeName>Charleston</placeName><lb/> I doubt if I receive one Cent from the<lb/> Congregation until after the arrival of those<lb/> other Books&#44; I fear I shall be compel&#39;d<lb/> &#39;ere another Year to again take the responsible<lb/> office of Parnass or I fear the worst result<lb/> to our Institution &#38; the standing of its Credit<lb/> I would prefer to never again resume office but a national<lb/> feeling will urge me on Its hard after so many<lb/> Years of hard Labour to make our People &#38; their</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>Institutions respected that others shall gain<lb/> the ascendancy &#38; be unable to keep up<lb/> its respectability.  I hope ere long to<lb/> give you a better account of your subscribers<lb/> here but they are hard to get money from<lb/> <persName>G. G. Levi</persName> I wrote a note to but <sic>He</sic><lb/> never called or <add>&#63;</add> me.  He is<lb/> going to reside in <placeName>Chicago Ill.</placeName><lb/>  I told you a <hi rend="underline">secret</hi> when the <sic>Body</sic> of <persName>Mr<lb/> Touro</persName> would leave here &#38; 2 <sic>Days</sic><lb/> after rec&#39;d your <date>May</date> Number &#38; perceived<lb/> It was public what was told me as<lb/> a profound Secret.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">Credit <persName>J P Hayes</persName> 3..00<lb/> <persName>Red J R Gutheim</persName> 3..00<lb/> <persName>L Goldsmith</persName> 3..00</p>
				<p>neither of these <sic>Have</sic> I recd the money from but<lb/> will do so next week &#38; I would like them<lb/> to be Credited in the <date>June</date> Number<lb/> <persName>Mr Goldsmith</persName> will at same time take his<lb/> Bible&#44; <persName>J. C. Labatt</persName> <sic>dont</sic> come<lb/> near me I shall again call<lb/> on him</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">May God Bless you &#38; grant<lb/> you many Years of Happiness is the<lb/> constant wish of your friend</p>
				<p><persName role="author">Isaac Hart</persName></p>
				<p rend="The following is written sideways in the left hand margin&#44; near the center of the page.">I enclose Duplicate<lb/> of Yesterday</p>
		</body>
